    <briefdescription>
<para>in the most general form, geodesic path can start in any mesh location (<ref refid="classMR_1_1MeshTriPoint" kindref="compound">MeshTriPoint</ref>), then pass triangles along straight lines, making turns on edges (MeshEdgePoint), and finish in any mesh location (<ref refid="classMR_1_1MeshTriPoint" kindref="compound">MeshTriPoint</ref>) Generated from class <computeroutput><ref refid="classMR_1_1GeodesicPath" kindref="compound">MR.GeodesicPath</ref></computeroutput>. This is the const half of the class. </para>
    </briefdescription>
